description: The Revd. William Favell, an old member of the college (matric. 1922), gave this illuminated French Psalter, CCCC MS 628, to Corpus Christi College in 1976. It was probably made in Paris c. 1240, certainly after 1234 because St Dominic, canonised in that year, is in the Litany. At the liturgical divisions of the Psalter there are eight fine full-page historiated initials. The figure style derives out of that of the artists of the Bibles moralises made for the French royal family in the period c. 1220-40.
